      "text": "She also distinguishes life from alive. She will mention that a screwdriver is life but not alive. I take this to mean a product made by alive entities to enable assemblies with a long history of selection. I made a screwdriver myself in high-school metal shop. It has a blade that only exists because there are screws to be turned. And it has a handle that exists because there are hands to hold it."
