      "text": "I make simple but useful programs of 50-100 lines. With few dependencies other than the computer that runs them, folks have suggested that they will have lasting value. I remind them just how complex the computers are and how much the sector learns about making computers in each of the seven decades I have been alive. Even the parts of a computer become computers in their own right soon enough. See Wheel of Reincarnation."
